content: Great app

This was a pleasant couple of hours but it was very short and relatively easy - i completed it in one sitting with no hints needed. Navigating around was tedious - i liked that you needed to jump back to previous locations, but there was no quick way to do so and it was hard to tell where you could walk to. It was annoying how your progress in a puzzle would reset whenever you looked at your notes and so you had to memorize the answer in one go.

As someone else said: clunky controls, less than ideal English, no ability to move between locations, very simple puzzles, somewhat short, not great looking, puzzles reset when checking notes, correct puzzles use audible cues which is bad when audio is off... basically, it lacks polish

This was a wonderful game. One of the best in it's genre. I have played all the games from syntaxity, but they felt a bit harder. This was of perfect difficulty level. The only thing I disliked is that the end is not perfect. It is like an incomplete story to be completed in the second game, Alice beyond wonderland. The balance between sound and music is also perfect!

This is how games of this genre should look like! No small areas to click, no illogical clues, automatic snapshoting of found clues, help system available for the worst case and skippable action-based puzzles. Gameplay, controls and graphics have some minor flaws, but I am giving 5 stars for the overall experience.
